Type and Style. There are lots of types available for sale, two major types are infants only and convertibles. It's a wise decision to find the one that can be used for child's growing years and the one which can be used long term.

Convertibles. Since children grow up really fast, it might be smart to buy convertibles. They can be easily used until the baby reaches 40 pounds of weight. They can be hooked in rear as well as front facing as they can accommodate the growing baby.

Infant Carrier. It is recommended to purchase the one that is infant carrier too. Sometimes the baby may go to sleep while you are out with your little one in infant carrier. You may not wish to wake up the infant to transfer him. Having the carrier as car seat will be added bonus when it comes to price and also you won't need to wake him to place him in a car.

Child car seat Reviews. Since there are lots of them available by many people different manufacturers, offering varied features that it can be rather a challenging task to choose the one for your baby. Reading reviews and comparing different options may help.